docs.abstract: Microsoft Word comes with many sample document templates, but you can also create your own custom letterhead.
docs.snippet: Microsoft Word comes with many sample document templates, but you can also create your own custom letterhead.
docs.lead_paragraph: Q. Microsoft Word 2016 comes with plenty of templates, but none of them are quite what I want. Is there a way to modify one of the stock business letters into a multipage document with my own letterhead?

headline.print_headline: Creating a Template Of Your Own

docs.abstract: New technologies are testing the limits of computer semiconductors. To deal with that, researchers have gone looking for ideas from nature.
docs.snippet: New technologies are testing the limits of computer semiconductors. To deal with that, researchers have gone looking for ideas from nature.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — We expect a lot from our computers these days. They should talk to us, recognize everything from faces to flowers, and maybe soon do the driving. All this artificial intelligence requires an enormous amount of computing power, stretching the limits of even the most modern machines.

headline.main: Chips Off the Old Block: Computers Are Taking Design Cues From Human Brains

docs.abstract: Two tech reporters analyze the week’s big tech news, including Uber’s surprising new C.E.O. and how Amazon might change Whole Foods.
docs.snippet: Two tech reporters analyze the week’s big tech news, including Uber’s surprising new C.E.O. and how Amazon might change Whole Foods.
docs.lead_paragraph: Each Friday, Farhad Manjoo and Mike Isaac, technology reporters at The New York Times, review the week’s news, offering analysis and maybe a joke or two about the most important developments in the tech industry. Mike is out this week so Nick Wingfield, a Times technology reporter based in Seattle, filled in.

headline.main: Farhad’s and Nick’s Week in Review: Uber’s New Boss and Amazon’s New Supermarket
headline.print_headline: Farhad’s and Nick’s Week in Review: A New Boss for Uber

byline.original: By Farhad Manjoo and Nick Wingfield
